                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13815/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dodge acknowledges telegram of June 18 and reports Oxley and Meyers detained
                    six days. Says the detention limit will not affect the detention of the Bailey
                    party.</p>
            </div>
